V 1.0.0-beta-8 - 2026-05-17

* V 1.0.0-beta-8

** `\custom <kind>=<sym> _mode=block` on non-paragraph markers (`¬ī`, `¬į`, `‚Äļ`) now defaults to single-newline body termination. Tables built with `¬ītd`-per-line work again.

* V 1.0.0-beta-7

** `\custom <kind>=<sym> ...` now auto-activates the marker for the tiddler ‚ÄĒ author defining custom behaviour implies the marker should fire.
** `_endString="\n"` (and `\r`, `\t`, `\\`, `\"`, `\'`) finally interprets the JS escapes instead of matching the literal `\n` characters.
** `_useGlobal=<sym>` switches to the global target wholesale; only local `_debug` wins, so the debug codeblock shows the resolved config.
** Trailing newline no longer leaks into widget `src` attribute or debug `text` codeblock when the terminator is eaten.

* V 1.0.0-beta-6

** `_use` and `_useGlobal` pragma aliases follow through to the target.
** `_debug=pragma|text|both|*Only|no` emits the pragma string and/or source slice as a code block.
** `¬į` `‚Äļ` default to single-newline body termination again; `¬Ľ` `‚Čą` `¬∂` to blank-line.

* V 1.0.0-beta-5

** `:"<arg>"` positional arguments after the symbol/class chain now feed `_params` widget attributes (`¬į‚ėź:"a"` overrides the first `_params` entry from the bridged pragma).
** Indirect / macro / filtered attribute values (`field={{!!yy}}`, `UID=<<qualify>>`) survive into the registry; previously stringified to `[object Object]`.
** Global `\custom` pragmas from `$:/config/custom-markup/pragma/PageTemplate` are loaded into every parser, restoring wiki-wide marker shortcuts (e.g. `¬įclip`, `¬įexample`).
** `¬Ľ` `‚Čą` `¬∂` markers wrap as `<p class="...">...</p>` again instead of `<div><p>...</p></div>`, matching the v0.x rendering.
** Widget `src` no longer carries a trailing newline (which became `%0A` in URL-valued attributes).

